olive oil
1 Avocado
2 Radish
1 sprig Spring Onion
1 packet Halloumi
1 tsp honey
1 packet balsamic glaze
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Slivered Almonds
1 packet Mint
1 packet diced bacon

• Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and thinly slice. Thinly slice radish and spring onion. Roughly chop roasted almonds.
• Peel and thinly slice orange into wedges.
• Cut halloumi into 1cm slices.

 • In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 4-6 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook halloumi, until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, add the honey and turn to coat.

 • In a medium bowl, combine balsamic & olive oil dressing, a drizzle of olive oil, a pinch of salt and pepper.
• To the bowl, add orange, radish, spring onion and mixed salad leaves. Sprinkle with diced bacon. Toss to combine.

• Divide orange and radish salad between bowls.
• Top with avocado and glazed halloumi. Sprinkle over roasted almonds. Tear over mint. Enjoy!